<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="59" type="distribution and ecology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Known only from the Andes of Venezuela (Lara, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mérida">Merida</normalizedToken>
, and Trujillo states) where it forms colonies in the understory of cloud forest; 1490-2600 (-3210) m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
This species is named for S. Miguel 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Niño">Nino</normalizedToken>
, professor at UNELLEZ, Guanare, and valued collaborator in our investigations of the Andean flora.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
